
## John Ackerman Olson

John Ackerman Olson (born 1964) is the Campbell and Jeanette Plugge endowed professor of surgery, head of the Division of General and Oncologic Surgery, and vice chairman of the Department of Surgery at the University of Maryland School of Medicine.

# Education and career 

Olson received his M.D. and Ph.D. degrees from the University of Florida College of Medicine in Gainesville, Florida and then did his training at Barnes-Jewish Hospital in St. Louis, Missouri. He then served as a registrar at the Royal Infirmary of Edinburgh and following it returned to New York where he worked at Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center. In 2000, Olson became an assistant professor at the Duke University School of Medicine, which was followed by an associate professor in 2005. Since 2012, Olson serves as professor of surgery at the University of Maryland School of Medicine and its subsidiaries in Easton, Towson and Glen Burnie.He is a senior member of the Society of Clinical Surgery and a fellow of the American College of Surgeons.

